28ResourceAdaptationProcessor::ResourceListenerDelegate::ResourceListenerDelegate(
29 ResourceAdaptationProcessor* processor)
30 : task_queue_(nullptr), processor_(processor) {}
31
32void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::ResourceListenerDelegate::SetTaskQueue(
33 TaskQueueBase* task_queue) {
34 RTC_DCHECK(!task_queue_);
35 RTC_DCHECK(task_queue);
36 task_queue_ = task_queue;
37 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
38}
39
40void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::ResourceListenerDelegate::
41 OnProcessorDestroyed() {
42 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
43 processor_ = nullptr;
44}
45
46void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::ResourceListenerDelegate::
47 OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource,
48 ResourceUsageState usage_state) {
49 if (!task_queue_->IsCurrent()) {
50 task_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
51 [this_ref = rtc::scoped_refptr<ResourceListenerDelegate>(this),
52 resource, usage_state] {
53 this_ref->OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(resource, usage_state);
54 }));
55 return;
56 }
57 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
58 if (processor_) {
59 processor_->OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(resource, usage_state);
60 }
61}

63ResourceAdaptationProcessor::MitigationResultAndLogMessage::
64 MitigationResultAndLogMessage()
65 : result(MitigationResult::kAdaptationApplied), message() {}
66
67ResourceAdaptationProcessor::MitigationResultAndLogMessage::
68 MitigationResultAndLogMessage(MitigationResult result, std::string message)
69 : result(result), message(std::move(message)) {}
70
71ResourceAdaptationProcessor::ResourceAdaptationProcessor(
72 VideoStreamAdapter* stream_adapter)
73 : task_queue_(nullptr),
74 resource_listener_delegate_(
75 rtc::make_ref_counted<ResourceListenerDelegate>(this)),
76 resources_(),
77 stream_adapter_(stream_adapter),
78 last_reported_source_restrictions_(),
79 previous_mitigation_results_() {
80 RTC_DCHECK(stream_adapter_);
81}
82
83ResourceAdaptationProcessor::~ResourceAdaptationProcessor() {
84 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
85 RTC_DCHECK(resources_.empty())
86 << "There are resource(s) attached to a ResourceAdaptationProcessor "
87 << "being destroyed.";
88 stream_adapter_->RemoveRestrictionsListener(this);
89 resource_listener_delegate_->OnProcessorDestroyed();
90}
91
92void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::SetTaskQueue(TaskQueueBase* task_queue) {
93 RTC_DCHECK(!task_queue_);
94 RTC_DCHECK(task_queue);
95 task_queue_ = task_queue;
96 resource_listener_delegate_->SetTaskQueue(task_queue);
97 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
98 // Now that we have the queue we can attach as adaptation listener.
99 stream_adapter_->AddRestrictionsListener(this);
100}
101
102void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::AddResourceLimitationsListener(
103 ResourceLimitationsListener* limitations_listener) {
104 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
105 RTC_DCHECK(std::find(resource_limitations_listeners_.begin(),
106 resource_limitations_listeners_.end(),
107 limitations_listener) ==
108 resource_limitations_listeners_.end());
109 resource_limitations_listeners_.push_back(limitations_listener);
110}
111
112void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::RemoveResourceLimitationsListener(
113 ResourceLimitationsListener* limitations_listener) {
114 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
115 auto it =
116 std::find(resource_limitations_listeners_.begin(),
117 resource_limitations_listeners_.end(), limitations_listener);
118 RTC_DCHECK(it != resource_limitations_listeners_.end());
119 resource_limitations_listeners_.erase(it);
120}
121
122void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::AddResource(
123 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource) {
124 RTC_DCHECK(resource);
125 {
126 MutexLock crit(&resources_lock_);
127 RTC_DCHECK(absl::c_find(resources_, resource) == resources_.end())
128 << "Resource \"" << resource->Name() << "\" was already registered.";
129 resources_.push_back(resource);
130 }
131 resource->SetResourceListener(resource_listener_delegate_);
132 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Registered resource \"" << resource->Name() << "\".";
133}
134
135std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>>
136ResourceAdaptationProcessor::GetResources() const {
137 MutexLock crit(&resources_lock_);
138 return resources_;
139}
140
141void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::RemoveResource(
142 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource) {
143 RTC_DCHECK(resource);
144 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Removing resource \"" << resource->Name() << "\".";
145 resource->SetResourceListener(nullptr);
146 {
147 MutexLock crit(&resources_lock_);
148 auto it = absl::c_find(resources_, resource);
149 RTC_DCHECK(it != resources_.end()) << "Resource \"" << resource->Name()
150 << "\" was not a registered resource.";
151 resources_.erase(it);
152 }
153 RemoveLimitationsImposedByResource(std::move(resource));
154}
155
156void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::RemoveLimitationsImposedByResource(
157 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource) {
158 if (!task_queue_->IsCurrent()) {
159 task_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
160 [this, resource]() { RemoveLimitationsImposedByResource(resource); }));
161 return;
162 }
163 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
164 auto resource_adaptation_limits =
165 adaptation_limits_by_resources_.find(resource);
166 if (resource_adaptation_limits != adaptation_limits_by_resources_.end()) {
167 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters adaptation_limits =
168 resource_adaptation_limits->second;
169 adaptation_limits_by_resources_.erase(resource_adaptation_limits);
170 if (adaptation_limits_by_resources_.empty()) {
171 // Only the resource being removed was adapted so clear restrictions.
172 stream_adapter_->ClearRestrictions();
173 return;
174 }
175
176 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters most_limited =
177 FindMostLimitedResources().second;
178
179 if (adaptation_limits.counters.Total() <= most_limited.counters.Total()) {
180 // The removed limitations were less limited than the most limited
181 // resource. Don't change the current restrictions.
182 return;
183 }
184
185 // Apply the new most limited resource as the next restrictions.
186 Adaptation adapt_to = stream_adapter_->GetAdaptationTo(
187 most_limited.counters, most_limited.restrictions);
188 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(adapt_to.status(), Adaptation::Status::kValid);
189 stream_adapter_->ApplyAdaptation(adapt_to, nullptr);
190
191 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Most limited resource removed. Restoring restrictions to "
192 "next most limited restrictions: "
193 << most_limited.restrictions.ToString() << " with counters "
194 << most_limited.counters.ToString();
195 }
196}
197
198void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(
199 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> resource,
200 ResourceUsageState usage_state) {
201 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
202 RTC_DCHECK(resource);
203 // |resource| could have been removed after signalling.
204 {
205 MutexLock crit(&resources_lock_);
206 if (absl::c_find(resources_, resource) == resources_.end()) {
207 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Ignoring signal from removed resource \""
208 << resource->Name() << "\".";
209 return;
210 }
211 }
212 MitigationResultAndLogMessage result_and_message;
213 switch (usage_state) {
214 case ResourceUsageState::kOveruse:
215 result_and_message = OnResourceOveruse(resource);
216 break;
217 case ResourceUsageState::kUnderuse:
218 result_and_message = OnResourceUnderuse(resource);
219 break;
220 }
221 // Maybe log the result of the operation.
222 auto it = previous_mitigation_results_.find(resource.get());
223 if (it != previous_mitigation_results_.end() &&
224 it->second == result_and_message.result) {
225 // This resource has previously reported the same result and we haven't
226 // successfully adapted since - don't log to avoid spam.
227 return;
228 }
229 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Resource \"" << resource->Name() << "\" signalled "
230 << ResourceUsageStateToString(usage_state) << ". "
231 << result_and_message.message;
232 if (result_and_message.result == MitigationResult::kAdaptationApplied) {
233 previous_mitigation_results_.clear();
234 } else {
235 previous_mitigation_results_.insert(
236 std::make_pair(resource.get(), result_and_message.result));
237 }
238}
239
240ResourceAdaptationProcessor::MitigationResultAndLogMessage
241ResourceAdaptationProcessor::OnResourceUnderuse(
242 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> reason_resource) {
243 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
244 // How can this stream be adapted up?
245 Adaptation adaptation = stream_adapter_->GetAdaptationUp();
246 if (adaptation.status() != Adaptation::Status::kValid) {
247 rtc::StringBuilder message;
248 message << "Not adapting up because VideoStreamAdapter returned "
249 << Adaptation::StatusToString(adaptation.status());
250 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(MitigationResult::kRejectedByAdapter,
251 message.Release());
252 }
253 // Check that resource is most limited.
254 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>> most_limited_resources;
255 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters most_limited_restrictions;
256 std::tie(most_limited_resources, most_limited_restrictions) =
257 FindMostLimitedResources();
258
259 // If the most restricted resource is less limited than current restrictions
260 // then proceed with adapting up.
261 if (!most_limited_resources.empty() &&
262 most_limited_restrictions.counters.Total() >=
263 stream_adapter_->adaptation_counters().Total()) {
264 // If |reason_resource| is not one of the most limiting resources then abort
265 // adaptation.
266 if (absl::c_find(most_limited_resources, reason_resource) ==
267 most_limited_resources.end()) {
268 rtc::StringBuilder message;
269 message << "Resource \"" << reason_resource->Name()
270 << "\" was not the most limited resource.";
271 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(
272 MitigationResult::kNotMostLimitedResource, message.Release());
273 }
274
275 if (most_limited_resources.size() > 1) {
276 // If there are multiple most limited resources, all must signal underuse
277 // before the adaptation is applied.
278 UpdateResourceLimitations(reason_resource, adaptation.restrictions(),
279 adaptation.counters());
280 rtc::StringBuilder message;
281 message << "Resource \"" << reason_resource->Name()
282 << "\" was not the only most limited resource.";
283 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(
284 MitigationResult::kSharedMostLimitedResource, message.Release());
285 }
286 }
287 // Apply adaptation.
288 stream_adapter_->ApplyAdaptation(adaptation, reason_resource);
289 rtc::StringBuilder message;
290 message << "Adapted up successfully. Unfiltered adaptations: "
291 << stream_adapter_->adaptation_counters().ToString();
292 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(MitigationResult::kAdaptationApplied,
293 message.Release());
294}
295
296ResourceAdaptationProcessor::MitigationResultAndLogMessage
297ResourceAdaptationProcessor::OnResourceOveruse(
298 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> reason_resource) {
299 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
300 // How can this stream be adapted up?
301 Adaptation adaptation = stream_adapter_->GetAdaptationDown();
302 if (adaptation.status() == Adaptation::Status::kLimitReached) {
303 // Add resource as most limited.
304 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters restrictions;
305 std::tie(std::ignore, restrictions) = FindMostLimitedResources();
306 UpdateResourceLimitations(reason_resource, restrictions.restrictions,
307 restrictions.counters);
308 }
309 if (adaptation.status() != Adaptation::Status::kValid) {
310 rtc::StringBuilder message;
311 message << "Not adapting down because VideoStreamAdapter returned "
312 << Adaptation::StatusToString(adaptation.status());
313 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(MitigationResult::kRejectedByAdapter,
314 message.Release());
315 }
316 // Apply adaptation.
317 UpdateResourceLimitations(reason_resource, adaptation.restrictions(),
318 adaptation.counters());
319 stream_adapter_->ApplyAdaptation(adaptation, reason_resource);
320 rtc::StringBuilder message;
321 message << "Adapted down successfully. Unfiltered adaptations: "
322 << stream_adapter_->adaptation_counters().ToString();
323 return MitigationResultAndLogMessage(MitigationResult::kAdaptationApplied,
324 message.Release());
325}
326
327std::pair<std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>>,
328 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters>
329ResourceAdaptationProcessor::FindMostLimitedResources() const {
330 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>> most_limited_resources;
331 VideoStreamAdapter::RestrictionsWithCounters most_limited_restrictions{
332 VideoSourceRestrictions(), VideoAdaptationCounters()};
333
334 for (const auto& resource_and_adaptation_limit_ :
335 adaptation_limits_by_resources_) {
336 const auto& restrictions_with_counters =
337 resource_and_adaptation_limit_.second;
338 if (restrictions_with_counters.counters.Total() >
339 most_limited_restrictions.counters.Total()) {
340 most_limited_restrictions = restrictions_with_counters;
341 most_limited_resources.clear();
342 most_limited_resources.push_back(resource_and_adaptation_limit_.first);
343 } else if (most_limited_restrictions.counters ==
344 restrictions_with_counters.counters) {
345 most_limited_resources.push_back(resource_and_adaptation_limit_.first);
346 }
347 }
348 return std::make_pair(std::move(most_limited_resources),
349 most_limited_restrictions);
350}
351
352void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::UpdateResourceLimitations(
353 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> reason_resource,
354 const VideoSourceRestrictions& restrictions,
355 const VideoAdaptationCounters& counters) {
356 auto& adaptation_limits = adaptation_limits_by_resources_[reason_resource];
357 if (adaptation_limits.restrictions == restrictions &&
358 adaptation_limits.counters == counters) {
359 return;
360 }
361 adaptation_limits = {restrictions, counters};
362
363 std::map<rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource>, VideoAdaptationCounters> limitations;
364 for (const auto& p : adaptation_limits_by_resources_) {
365 limitations.insert(std::make_pair(p.first, p.second.counters));
366 }
367 for (auto limitations_listener : resource_limitations_listeners_) {
368 limitations_listener->OnResourceLimitationChanged(reason_resource,
369 limitations);
370 }
371}
372
373void ResourceAdaptationProcessor::OnVideoSourceRestrictionsUpdated(
374 VideoSourceRestrictions restrictions,
375 const VideoAdaptationCounters& adaptation_counters,
376 rtc::scoped_refptr<Resource> reason,
377 const VideoSourceRestrictions& unfiltered_restrictions) {
378 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(task_queue_);
379 if (reason) {
380 UpdateResourceLimitations(reason, unfiltered_restrictions,
381 adaptation_counters);
382 } else if (adaptation_counters.Total() == 0) {
383 // Adaptations are cleared.
384 adaptation_limits_by_resources_.clear();
385 previous_mitigation_results_.clear();
386 for (auto limitations_listener : resource_limitations_listeners_) {
387 limitations_listener->OnResourceLimitationChanged(nullptr, {});
388 }
389 }
390}
